Ingredients
Potatoes: 2 lbs (Yukon Gold or Russet recommended)
Cabbage/Kale: 3-4 cups shredded cabbage (savoy or green) or kale
Butter: 4-8 tbsp (preferably Irish, such as Kerrygold)
Milk/Cream: - 1 cup (whole milk, half-and-half, or cream)
Scallions/Leeks: 1 bunch scallions (chopped) or 2-3 leeks (white/light green parts)
Seasoning: Salt and pepper to taste
Optional: 4 slices of bacon, cooked and crumbled 

Instructions
Prep and Boil Potatoes: Peel (optional) and cut 2 lbs of potatoes into chunks. Place in a pot of cold salted water, bring to a boil, and cook until tender, roughly 15–20 minutes.
Sauté Greens: While potatoes cook, melt 2–3 tbsp of butter in a skillet. Add 1 bunch of sliced scallions (or chopped leeks) and sauté for 2-3 minutes. Add 3–4 cups of shredded cabbage or kale and cook until wilted and tender.
Mash Potatoes: Drain the potatoes and return them to the hot pot to steam dry for 1–2 minutes. Mash with 

 cup milk/cream and 2-3 tbsp butter until smooth or slightly chunky.
Combine: Mix the sautéed cabbage/greens into the mashed potatoes. Add the remaining butter and scallion greens.
Season and Serve: Season generously with salt and black pepper. Make a well in the center and add an extra pat of butter before serving. 
